<h3 id="which-factors">Which Factors?</h3>

<h4 id="æ¦‚è¿°-1">æ¦‚è¿°</h4>

<blockquote>
  <ul>
    <li>Many recently proposed, seemingly different factor models are closely related. 
 In spanning tests, the q-factor model largely subsumes the Famaâ€“French five- and six-factor models, 
 and the q5 model subsumes the Stambaughâ€“Yuan four-factor model. 
 Their â€œmispricingâ€ factors are sensitive to the construction procedure, 
 and once replicated via the traditional approach, are close to the q-factors, 
 with correlations of 0.8 and 0.84. Finally, consistent with the investment CAPM, 
 valuation theory predicts a positive relation between the expected investment 
 and the expected return. 
